  "text": "Its ubiquitous expression facilitates the assessment of sex chromosome-specific expression of HSYPR3 in somatic cell hybrids retaining a Y or an active or inactive X chromosome as the sole human DNA [CITATION_1] . RT-PCR assays with primers derived from exons 1 and 2 demonstrated that the gene, like the nearby SYBL1 gene [CITATION_2] , is subject to X inactivation (Fig. 2) . Apparently, X inactivation is maintained in all of zone 1 (see Discussion).",
